[normal]              
[normal]The key to our industry—ignoring geological gas-flow scenarios etc—is the economics.  The economics improve when we get the supply chain to a point where that is economic.  Part of my role over the course of the next two years is to start looking at the supply chain.  I am working with BIS on various different studies in terms of the supply chain.  I will give you one example.  2,000 rigs are working onshore in the 
[normal]US
[normal].  We have 77 in the entirety of Europe, and probably about 10 working now in the 
[normal]UK
[normal].  We are going to need somewhere between 100 and 200 rigs in the 
[normal]UK
[normal] over the course of the next decade.  We have a choice: we can make them here in the 
[normal]UK
[normal] or we can buy them elsewhere.  I would like to try to build them in the 
[normal]UK
[normal],
[normal] economically
[normal],
[normal] for our industry.  As I said, we are working with
[normal] 
[normal]BIS on that.  
